subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Foenatopus menglongensis
, but 
Foenatopus maculiferus
has the two pale patches of the third metasomal tergite (absent in 
Foenatopus menglongensis
), the scutellum convex medially (flat in 
Foenatopus menglongensis
), the propodeum rather matt (shiny in 
Foenatopus menglongensis
) and the hind femur comparatively slender (comparatively swollen in 
Foenatopus menglongensis
).
